    <title>Combined summary - Scaling Lightning With Simple Covenants</title>
    <updated>2023-09-28T01:56:30.505206+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2023-September/004117.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The email exchange focuses on improving capital efficiency in Lightning Network channels by proposing changes to the Bitcoin consensus rules. Antoine raises questions about potential security vulnerabilities and scenarios where one party could harm another party in collusion. He also compares the TP protocol's security model to other off-chain constructions. Antoine suggests different scaling notions and highlights difficulties in group coordination among casual users. The email discusses the cost of enforcement, the tradeoff between trust and capital efficiency, and the challenges of scaling Lightning in a trust-free manner. Proposed solutions include introducing different scaling notions, implementing timeout-trees, and adding mechanisms to Bitcoin's consensus rules.</summary>
